This paper deals with lidar sensors used in autonomous vehicles and mobile robotics, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a CNN-based approach to filter out adverse weather effects in point cloud data, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The use of a large dataset and performance improvement over state-of-the-art methods suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques to describe the problem and solution, which could fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL).
